metadata.name: The Leopard's Face
metadata.description:
Hip ornament in the form of a leopard's face, worn by the military chiefs of the ancient Kingdom of Benin and was bestowed onto them by the Oba (king).

The wearer of this ornament had the authority to act in the Oba's name. 

**Production Date:** 16th Century 

**Technique:** Lost-Wax Method
